Package: survAudit
Title: Auditing and Transparency Framework for Cox Proportional Hazards Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Gregor", "Miller", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "gregor.miller@uk-augsburg.de")
Description: Provides a unified diagnostic auditing framework for Cox 
    proportional hazards models. Automates proportional hazards testing, 
    functional form assessment, influence diagnostics, outlier detection, 
    and event sufficiency checks. Implements a structured assumption ontology 
    that explicitly classifies model assumptions as statistically assessable, 
    partially assessable, or non-identifiable, encouraging transparent 
    reporting of unverifiable assumptions alongside data-driven diagnostics.
